data.description: Two expansive residences, situated on a generous four-acre lot in Felton Borough, present a unique and extraordinary opportunity. This compound is ideally suited for accommodating multiple families, offering ample living space. The two homes are strategically positioned over 300 feet apart, complemented by a bank barn in need of some tender loving care (TLC) and a beautiful cabin.  The first home, located at 29 High Street, is a colonial-style residence spanning about 1,740 sq ft. Originally a duplex, has been converted into a single-family home with four bedrooms and one and a half baths. The first floor includes a large foyer/entrance way, kitchen, dining room and large living room adorned with exposed wood beams. The small bedroom on the first floor could be used as home office. Upstairs includes 3 bedrooms and a family room that the owners used as the primary bedroom featuring a spacious walk-in closet/sunroom, and a private staircase. The large basement was previously used as a woodworking shop, and a substantial walk-up attic adds to the property's versatility. A newly installed 6ft fence connects 29 High to the barn, providing a cohesive and secure environment.  The second home, located at 31 High Street, is a charming cabin spanning about 1,760 sq. ft. It boasts three bedrooms and two full baths, including an open chef's kitchen with a breakfast bar, a dining area, and a living room – an entertainer's delight. The first floor encompasses a convenient laundry and full bath, while the second floor offers a spacious open loft, a full bath with a claw foot tub, and two bedrooms. The primary bedroom occupies the third floor and features two catwalk balconies, with the fourth-floor space cleverly converted into a hidden sleeping area above the master. Surrounded by the tranquility of nature, this home provides a private retreat, complete with a creek running through the property and park-like settings. Outdoor entertainment areas, including fire pits, enhance the overall experience. Consider the prospect of renting one home while residing in the other, creating an opportunity for additional income. Don't miss out on this once-in-a-lifetime chance to own a property that combines spacious living, natural beauty, and potential financial benefits of living in one and renting the other!
